No's. 6,8,10,12,14, and 12 Broome Street, at, adjoining and west of the N. W. corner of Tompkins Street. Also shown is Tompkins Street, west side, north from Broome to Delancey Streets. Note the East River (Williamsburg) Bridge arching Tompkins Street. These buildings are numbered as above. The corner block is 6 to 14 inclusive.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)
Tompkins Street, west side, north from Broome, to Delancey Streets, as seen from clearance on the east side of street. Note the Williamsburg Bridge Approach on Delancey Street.
March 29, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, from a different angle. Also shown is Broome Street, north side, west from and including Tompkins to and including Mangin Streets.
March 29, 1936.
